QUANTUM EDGE NEUROMORPHIC ENGINE (QUENNE) SATELLITE DATA CENTER

COMPREHENSIVE TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS DOCUMENT

Version 3.1 | Classification: QUENNE-RESTRICTED | Date: April 2026

---

EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

The QUANTUM EDGE NEUROMORPHIC ENGINE (QUENNE) represents humanity's first multi-century computational platform, designed for autonomous operation in the space environment. This document outlines the complete technical specifications for a constellation of 1,024 interconnected satellites forming a distributed quantum-neuromorphic supercomputer with interplanetary capabilities.

---

1. MISSION OBJECTIVES & REQUIREMENTS

1.1 Primary Mission Objectives

```
1. Create a self-sustaining computational infrastructure operable for 500-1000 years
2. Establish an interplanetary quantum communication backbone
3. Provide distributed computing resources for deep space research
4. Preserve human knowledge and culture across millennial timescales
5. Enable autonomous scientific discovery beyond human lifespans
6. Serve as a testbed for interstellar communication technologies
```

1.2 Operational Requirements

Parameter Minimum Requirement Target Specification Units
Operational Lifetime 100 years 500-1000 years years
Uptime (per satellite) 99.99% 99.999% %
Radiation Tolerance 1000 krad (Si) 10,000 krad (Si) total dose
Temperature Range -150°C to +150°C -200°C to +200°C °C
Autonomous Operation 30 days 10 years without ground contact
Data Integrity 10^-15 BER 10^-18 BER bit error rate
Quantum Coherence 1 ms 500 ms T₂ time

