3. QUANTUM COMPUTING SUBSYSTEM

3.1 Quantum Processing Unit (QPU) Specifications

```
QPU ARCHITECTURE: Superconducting Transmon with Photonic Interconnect

PHYSICAL PARAMETERS:
• Qubit Type: Fixed-frequency transmons with tunable couplers
• Operating Temperature: 10 mK (dilution refrigerator)
• Cryostat Volume: 1.5 m³
• Cooling Power: 5 μW at 100 mK, 50 mW at 4K

QUBIT PERFORMANCE:
• Physical Qubits per Satellite: 8,192
• Logical Qubits per Satellite: 1,024 (8:1 encoding ratio)
• Coherence Times:
  - T₁ (energy relaxation): 300 μs
  - T₂ (dephasing time): 500 μs
  - T₂* (Ramsey dephasing): 200 μs
• Gate Fidelities:
  - Single-qubit gates: 99.995%
  - Two-qubit gates: 99.9%
  - Readout fidelity: 99.5%
• Gate Times:
  - Single-qubit: 20 ns
  - Two-qubit (CZ): 40 ns
  - Measurement: 500 ns

ERROR CORRECTION:
• Code: Surface-17 (distance 3)
• Logical Error Rate: 10^-8 per cycle
• Cycle Time: 1 μs
• Ancilla Qubits: 25% of physical qubits

INTERCONNECT:
• On-chip: Superconducting coaxial resonators
• Inter-chip: Microwave-over-fiber (20 GHz bandwidth)
• Inter-satellite: Entangled photon distribution (1550 nm)
```

3.2 Quantum Memory Specifications

```
QUANTUM MEMORY SYSTEM:
• Type: Atomic ensemble with EIT (Electromagnetically Induced Transparency)
• Medium: Rubidium-87 vapor cell
• Storage Time: 10 seconds (room temperature), 1000 seconds (cryogenic)
• Bandwidth: 10 MHz
• Efficiency: 80% (write), 70% (read)
• Multiplexing: 1000 temporal modes
• Capacity: 1000 qubits stored simultaneously
• Interface: Quantum frequency conversion to telecom band

QUANTUM RANDOM ACCESS MEMORY (QRAM):
• Architecture: Bucket brigade tree with superconducting resonators
• Capacity: 1024 addressable quantum registers
• Access Time: 100 ns
• Power Consumption: 10 mW per access
```

3.3 Quantum Network Specifications

```
QUANTUM COMMUNICATION PARAMETERS:

Entanglement Generation:
• Source: SPDC (Spontaneous Parametric Down-Conversion)
• Pair Rate: 10^7 pairs/second
• Wavelength: 1550 nm (telecom C-band)
• Entanglement Fidelity: 99%
• Brightness: 10^6 pairs/(s·mW·MHz)

Free-Space Quantum Links:
• Terminal Aperture: 30 cm
• Beam Divergence: 5 μrad
• Pointing Accuracy: 0.1 μrad
• Tracking Bandwidth: 1 kHz
• Link Budget (1000 km range):
  - Transmit Power: 1 mW
  - Loss: 40 dB (atmospheric + pointing + diffraction)
  - Received Photons: 10^-4 per pulse
• Key Distribution Rate: 100 kbps (secure)

Quantum Repeaters:
• Type: Memory-based with entanglement swapping
• Storage Time: >1 second
• Entanglement Purification: 2→1 protocol
• Fidelity Improvement: 90% → 99%
• Node Spacing: 1000 km (ground), 10,000 km (space)
```

