4. NEUROMORPHIC COMPUTING SUBSYSTEM

4.1 Neuromorphic Core Specifications

```
NEUROMORPHIC PROCESSOR ARCHITECTURE: Event-driven Spiking Neural Network

CORE COMPONENTS:
• Number of Cores: 4,096 per satellite
• Neurons per Core: 256
• Total Neurons: 1,048,576 per satellite
• Synapses per Neuron: 1,024 (configurable 256-4096)
• Total Synapses: 1.07 × 10^9 per satellite

NEURON MODEL:
• Type: Leaky Integrate-and-Fire (LIF) with adaptive thresholds
• Parameters:
  - Membrane time constant (τ_m): 20 ms
  - Reset voltage: -65 mV
  - Threshold voltage: -50 mV
  - Resting potential: -70 mV
  - Refractory period: 2 ms
• Learning Rules:
  - STDP (Spike-Timing-Dependent Plasticity): Δw = A⁺e^(-Δt/τ⁺) - A⁻e^(Δt/τ⁻)
  - Homeostatic plasticity: BCM rule with sliding threshold
  - Structural plasticity: Probabilistic synapse formation/elimination

SYNAPSE TECHNOLOGY:
• Weight Storage: Phase-change memory (PCM)
• Resistance Range: 10 kΩ to 10 MΩ
• Endurance: 10^12 write cycles
• Retention: >10 years at 85°C
• Multi-level capability: 4 bits (16 levels) per synapse

EVENT ROUTING FABRIC:
• Topology: 2D mesh with hierarchical routing
• Router Buffer Size: 64 spike packets
• Routing Latency: 10 ns (nearest neighbor), 100 ns (worst case)
• Bandwidth: 1 Tbps aggregate
• Deadlock Avoidance: Virtual channel flow control
```

