5. CLASSICAL COMPUTING SUBSYSTEM

5.1 Central Processing Units

```
PROCESSOR ARCHITECTURE: Heterogeneous Multi-Core

MAIN PROCESSORS (2×):
• Architecture: ARM Neoverse V2 (radiation-hardened)
• Cores: 128 cores per processor (256 total)
• Clock Speed: 3.0 GHz (nominal), 1.5 GHz (radiation-safe)
• Cache:
  - L1: 64 KB I/D per core
  - L2: 512 KB per core
  - L3: 256 MB shared
• SIMD: SVE2 (Scalable Vector Extension), 512-bit vectors
• Process Node: 5 nm FinFET (radiation-hardened)
• TDP: 250 W per processor (500 W total)

ACCELERATOR PROCESSORS:
• GPU: 4× NVIDIA Orin-like (radiation-hardened)
  - CUDA Cores: 2048 per GPU (8192 total)
  - Tensor Cores: 64 per GPU (256 total)
  - Memory: 32 GB HBM2e per GPU (128 GB total)
  - TFLOPS: 200 FP32 per GPU (800 total)
  
• FPGA: 2× Xilinx Versal AI Edge (radiation-hardened)
  - Adaptive Compute Engines: 400 per FPGA
  - AI Engines: 128 per FPGA
  - DSP Engines: 1964 per FPGA
  - Memory: 32 GB DDR4 per FPGA

• ASIC Accelerators:
  - Cryptography: 100 Gbps AES-256, Post-quantum crypto
  - Compression: 200 Gbps lossless, 50:1 typical ratio
  - Signal Processing: 1000-channel real-time processing
```

5.2 Memory and Storage

```
SYSTEM MEMORY:
• Type: Radiation-hardened DDR5 with ECC
