7. THERMAL MANAGEMENT SYSTEM

7.1 Heat Generation Profile

```
HEAT SOURCES:
• Quantum Subsystem: 500 W (at 4K), 2,000 W (rejected at 300K)
• Neuromorphic Subsystem: 2,000 W (at 300K)
• Classical Subsystem: 5,000 W (at 300K)
• Fusion Reactor: 30 MW thermal → 20 MW electrical + 10 MW waste heat
• Total Waste Heat: 12,000 W (excluding reactor conversion losses)

HEAT DENSITY:
• Quantum Processors: 100 W/cm² (localized, cryogenic)
• Neuromorphic Chips: 50 W/cm²
• CPU/GPU: 100 W/cm²
• Memory: 10 W/cm²
• Storage: 5 W/cm²
```

7.2 Cooling Systems

```
MULTI-STAGE COOLING ARCHITECTURE:

STAGE 1: CRYOGENIC (Quantum Processors)
• Temperature Range: 10 mK to 4K
• Method: Dilution refrigerator with pulse tube precooler
• Cooling Power:
  - 5 μW at 100 mK
  - 50 mW at 4K
• Coolant: Helium-3/Helium-4 mixture
• Compressor Power: 2,000 W (input for 50 mW at 4K)

STAGE 2: LOW-TEMPERATURE (Superconducting Magnets)
• Temperature Range: 4K to 80K
• Method: Closed-cycle helium cryocooler
• Cooling Power: 100 W at 80K
• Coolant: Helium gas
• Compressor Power: 1,000 W

STAGE 3: INTERMEDIATE (Electronics)
• Temperature Range: 80K to 200K
• Method: Brayton cycle with neon refrigerant
• Cooling Power: 1,000 W at 200K
• Compressor Power: 500 W

STAGE 4: ROOM TEMPERATURE (General Electronics)
• Temperature Range: 200K to 300K
• Method: Pumped two-phase loop with ammonia
• Cooling Power: 10,000 W
• Pump Power: 100 W

STAGE 5: HIGH TEMPERATURE (Power Systems)
• Temperature Range: 300K to 500K
• Method: Heat pipes with sodium working fluid
• Heat Transport: 50,000 W
• No moving parts

HEAT REJECTION:
• Primary: Deployable radiators
• Area: 48 m² (8 panels × 6 m² each)
• Temperature: 300K (nominal), up to 500K (peak)
• Emissivity: 0.95 (carbon nanotube coating)
• Heat Rejection: 12,000 W at 300K, 50,000 W at 500K
• Redundancy: 100% (dual-loop system)
```

7.3 Thermal Control Algorithms

```
ADAPTIVE THERMAL MANAGEMENT:
• Control Method: Model Predictive Control (MPC) with quantum optimization
• Sensors: 1000+ temperature points, 100+ heat flux sensors
• Actuators: Variable speed pumps, flow control valves, electrocaloric coolers
• Response Time: <1 second for local adjustments, <10 seconds for system-wide

PREDICTIVE THERMAL LOAD BALANCING:
• Algorithm: Quantum annealing for workload distribution
• Inputs: Computational schedule, orbital position, solar flux
• Output: Optimal processor mapping to minimize hot spots
• Update Frequency: 1 Hz (continuous optimization)

EMERGENCY COOLING:
• Phase Change Materials: Paraffin wax (melting at 50°C)
• Capacity: 1 MJ per satellite
• Activation: Automatic during cooling system failure
• Duration: 30 minutes at full load
```

