11. RELIABILITY & REDUNDANCY

11.1 Reliability Requirements

```
RELIABILITY METRICS:
• Mission Success Probability: >0.99 for 10 years, >0.90 for 100 years
• Mean Time Between Failures (MTBF): >100,000 hours per satellite
• Mean Time To Repair (MTTR): <24 hours (automated), <7 days (with ground support)
• Availability: 99.99% per satellite, 99.999% for constellation
• Data Integrity: 10^-18 bit error rate
• Quantum State Fidelity: >0.99 maintained for 1000 years

SINGLE EVENT EFFECTS (SEE) PROTECTION:
• Latch-up Immunity: >100 MeV·cm²/mg (LET threshold)
• Single Event Upset (SEU) Rate: <10^-10 errors/bit-day
• Single Event Functional Interrupt (SEFI): <1 per 10,000 years
• Total Ionizing Dose (TID): 10,000 krad (Si) with <10% degradation
```

11.2 Redundancy Architecture

```
REDUNDANCY STRATEGY: N+2 with Graceful Degradation

QUANTUM SUBSYSTEM:
• QPUs: 3× (2 active, 1 standby)
• Cryocoolers: 4× (2+2 configuration)
• Control Electronics: Triple modular redundancy with voting
• Memory: ECC with chipkill and spare rows/columns

NEUROMORPHIC SUBSYSTEM:
• Cores: 20% spares (distributed)
• Routing: 2× interconnect fabrics (primary + backup)
• Power: Dual-rail with cross-strapping

CLASSICAL SUBSYSTEM:
• Processors: N+1 with hot swap capability
• Memory: RAID-like with distributed parity
• Storage: Erasure coding (10+2 Reed-Solomon)
• Network: Multiple paths with automatic failover

POWER SYSTEM:
• Reactors: 2× (one active, one cold spare)
• Distribution: Triple modular with majority voting
• Batteries: 2× capacity requirement
• Solar Arrays: 4× strings with cross-strapping

COMMUNICATIONS:
• Transceivers: 2× per band (active/standby)
• Antennas: 2× per type with overlapping coverage
• Processors: Triple modular with bit-wise comparison
```

11.3 Failure Detection & Recovery

```
FAILURE DETECTION:
• Method: Continuous health monitoring with ML anomaly detection
• Sensors: 10,000+ points per satellite
• Sampling Rate: 1 kHz (critical), 1 Hz (non-critical)
• Latency: <100 ms for critical failures
• False Positive Rate: <10^-6 per day

AUTONOMOUS RECOVERY:
• Level 1: Component reset (microseconds)
• Level 2: Module failover (milliseconds)
• Level 3: System reconfiguration (seconds)
• Level 4: Constellation reorganization (minutes)
• Level 5: Mission replanning (hours)

SELF-HEALING MECHANISMS:
• Software: Automatic patching with rollback capability
• Hardware: Nanobot repair for physical damage
• Configuration: Evolutionary optimization of system parameters
• Data: Automatic repair from distributed parity
```

