15.1 Space Debris Mitigation

```
DEBRIS MITIGATION STRATEGY:
• Design for Demise: >95% of satellite mass burns up on reentry
• End-of-Life Disposal: Graveyard orbit at 500 km above operational orbit
• Collision Avoidance: Automated with >99.9% probability of success
• Passivation: Complete depletion of energy sources before disposal
• Tracking: Continuous with onboard sensors and ground-based SSA

COLLISION AVOIDANCE SYSTEM:
• Sensors: Radar, lidar, optical cameras
• Detection Range: 1000 km for objects >10 cm
• Tracking Capacity: 1000 objects simultaneously
• Maneuver Capability: 1 m/s per week allocated for avoidance
• Decision Time: <1 hour from detection to execution

DEBRIS GENERATION CONTROL:
• No Explosives: Safe separation mechanisms only
• Secured Components: All items fastened to prevent release
• Material Selection: Low-outgassing, non-fragmenting materials
• Testing: Hypervelocity impact testing of all components
```

