```
EMI/EMC REQUIREMENTS:
• Emissions: Compliant with ITU Radio Regulations
• Susceptibility: Hardened against solar flares and nuclear EMP
• Frequency Coordination: Registered with ITU and national agencies
• Spectrum Management: Dynamic frequency assignment to avoid interference

INTERFERENCE MITIGATION:
• Beam Steering: Narrow beams to minimize spillover
• Frequency Agility: Automatic switching to avoid conflicts
• Power Control: Adaptive based on link conditions
• Coordination: Real-time with other satellite operators
```

15.3 Planetary Protection

```
CONTAMINATION CONTROL:
• Forward Contamination: Sterilization to Category IV requirements
• Backward Contamination: No sample return from alien worlds
• Cleanroom Assembly: Class 100 (ISO 5) for critical components
• Biobarriers: Multiple layers with periodic integrity checks

STERILIZATION METHODS:
• Heat: Dry heat microbial reduction (DHMR) at 125°C for 24 hours
• Radiation: Gamma irradiation at 25 kGy
• Chemical: Vapor hydrogen peroxide (VHP) treatment
• Verification: Biological indicators and ATP testing
