17. RISK MANAGEMENT

17.1 Technical Risks

```
HIGH RISKS:
1. Quantum Decoherence in Space Environment
   • Probability: Medium (0.3)
   • Impact: High (0.8)
   • Mitigation: Redundant error correction, active shielding
   • Contingency: Fallback to classical simulation

2. Fusion Reactor Reliability
   • Probability: Medium (0.4)
   • Impact: High (0.9)
   • Mitigation: Extensive ground testing, dual reactors
   • Contingency: Solar/battery backup for reduced operations

3. Radiation Damage Accumulation
   • Probability: High (0.7)
   • Impact: Medium (0.6)
   • Mitigation: Self-repair systems, component hardening
   • Contingency: Evolutionary hardware adaptation

MEDIUM RISKS:
4. Software Complexity Management
5. Inter-satellite Link Reliability
6. Thermal Management Under Load
7. Launch Vehicle Availability
8. Supply Chain Disruptions

LOW RISKS:
9. Orbital Debris Collisions
10. Power System Failures
11. Ground Station Reliability
12. Human Error in Operations
```

17.2 Programmatic Risks

```
SCHEDULE RISKS:
• Critical Path: Quantum processor development (24 months margin)
• Integration Complexity: 18 months contingency
• Launch Delays: 12 months buffer in deployment schedule
• Regulatory Approval: Early engagement with ITU, FCC, etc.

COST RISKS:
• Technology Development: 50% contingency on R&D
• Production Learning Curve: 20% reduction expected over first 100 units
• Launch Costs: Fixed-price contracts with multiple providers
• Currency Fluctuation: Hedging strategy for international purchases

PARTNER RISKS:
• Technology Lock-in: Open standards and multiple sources
• Geopolitical Issues: Distributed manufacturing across regions
• Intellectual Property: Clear agreements and open-source where possible
• Export Controls: Early classification and compliance planning
```

17.3 Risk Mitigation Strategies

```
PROACTIVE MITIGATION:
• Technology Demos: Subscale prototypes before full commitment
• Design Margins: 30-50% margins on critical parameters
• Redundancy: N+2 on all critical systems
• Testing: Extensive environmental testing beyond requirements
• Modeling: High-fidelity simulations of all failure modes

REACTIVE MITIGATION:
• Anomaly Response Teams: 24/7 on-call for critical systems
• Spares Inventory: Orbit
```
